## Refactoring Rules

### When to Refactor
- Code duplicated 3+ times (DRY it)
- Function/module exceeds size limits
- Unclear names or confusing logic
- Adding feature is difficult

### How to Refactor
1. {% if include_tests %}Ensure tests exist first{% else %}Test current functionality{% endif +%}
2. Make small, incremental changes
3. {% if include_tests %}Test after each change{% else %}Test frequently during refactoring{% endif +%}
4. Commit working states frequently
5. Don't change behavior (unless fixing bugs)

## Emergency Procedures

### Critical Bug in Production
1. Create `hotfix/*` branch from `main`
2. Fix minimal code to resolve issue
3. Test thoroughly
4. Fast-track review
5. Deploy immediately
6. Merge back to `main` and `develop`
7. Document in CHANGELOG

### Game Won't Launch / Crashes on Startup
1. Check for missing or corrupt asset files{% if has_sprites %} (`assets/images/`){% endif %}{% if has_sound %}{% if has_sprites %} and{% endif %} (`assets/sounds/`){% endif +%}
2. Verify the game framework and its dependencies are installed (`pip install -r requirements.txt`)
3. Check logs{% if has_logging %} in `logs/{{ project_name | snake_case }}.log`{% endif %} for the traceback
4. Roll back to the last known-good commit if the cause isn't obvious

